    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-12T23:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-12T23:47:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11591: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander of the United States Yangtze Patrol</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marquart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="54" xml:id="d625fn54">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Above Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName> ] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-13T12:47:00+08:00"
                            >December 13, 1937—12:47 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 13—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0013. Have urged Hashimoto<note n="55" xml:id="d625fn55">Col. Kingoro Hashimoto,
                        Japanese Army officer.</note> through British at Wuhu not attack Hohsien
                    until American and other foreign refugees have been embarked. Expect <hi
                        rend="italic">Oahu</hi> arrive Wuhu early tomorrow morning and have
                    requested British convey this information to local Jap authorities.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
